This paper is about optimizing neural networks for binary classification, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper focuses on shallow networks, which are often used for simple classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to the design and analysis of algorithms for learning from data. Other likely sub-categories include cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which are all relevant to the topic of optimizing neural networks for classification.
